## When to use
Use this skill when you need to monitor CPU and I/O statistics of your Linux system to analyze its performance.

## Approach
To monitor system resources, use the `shell_exec` tool to run the `iostat` command with appropriate parameters. This allows for real-time analysis of disk usage and overall system load.

## Example
```yaml
- shell_exec: "iostat -x 1"
```

## Pitfalls
Running `iostat` frequently can introduce a small overhead on your system, impacting the very metrics you are measuring. Be mindful of this when using short intervals like `-d 1`.